6 Subject: Crimes; animal cruelty; penalties
7 Statement of purpose of bill as introduced: This bill proposes to supplement
8 the penalties and crimes related to animal cruelty. Specifically, this bill
9 proposes to require that a person convicted of animal cruelty or aggravated
10 animal cruelty be dispossessed of any animal in the person’s possession and be
11 prohibited from possessing or owning any animal in the future. Further, this
12 bill proposes to introduce the concept of “coercive control” within the animal
13 cruelty context. As a result, this bill proposes that persons who commit or
14 threaten to commit animal cruelty upon an animal to influence a victim of
15 domestic abuse may face additional criminal penalties.
